The paper discusses the reliability and lifetime improvement of solid-state drives (SSDs) that use NAND flash memory. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as well as the sub-categories of Architecture (cs.AR), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper discusses experimental data and techniques for error characterization, mitigation, and data recovery, which are relevant to these sub-categories.
